CDC in CDA is derived from the SCD history, so the validation should focus on whether the CDC output correctly reflects the changes captured in SCD.

Please check the following:

Pick a few business keys from each available domain.
Verify the first occurrence of a business key results in an INSERT.
If the same business key has multiple SCD versions, verify each actual data change results in a corresponding UPDATE in the CDC output.
Ensure no CDC event is generated when there is no change in business attributes.
Verify the sequence of CDC events follows the SCD version/effective timestamp order.
Check for any duplicate CDC events for the same change.
If delete scenarios exist, verify they are represented as expected by the Guidewire CDC design.

The objective is to confirm that every change captured in the SCD history is correctly represented in the derived CDC output.
